TY  - JOUR
AU  - Chen, Yao-Tsung
AU  - Wu, Chunchi
AU  - Yeh, Chung-Ying
T1  - Asset Pricing Tests of Infrequently Traded Securities: The Case of Municipal Bonds
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rapstu/raac002
JO  - The Review of Asset Pricing Studies
JA  - Rev Asset Pric Stud
VL  - 12
IS  - 3
SP  - 754
EP  - 807
SN  - 2045-9920
AB  - Using a dynamic selection model, we obtain consistent and unbiased estimates of risk and returns for infrequently traded bonds and conduct the first comprehensive asset pricing test of municipal bonds using the multifactor approach. Correction for sample selection and infrequent trading problems results in substantially higher beta estimates. Besides conventional risk factors, illiquidity and taxes are important for the pricing of municipal bonds. Importantly, bond returns contain a significant liquidity risk premium. Failing to account for sample selection bias leads to erroneous inference on the magnitude of systematic risk and substantial underestimation of risk premiums. (JEL G12, G14)
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rapstu/raac002
ER  - 



